  "title": "Sales Intern",
  "description": "<p><strong>Overview</strong><br />To build a pipeline of potential customers and provide administrative relief to Directors.<br /><br /><strong>Job Description</strong><br /><strong>1. Lead Generation & Prospecting</strong><br />Identify potential clients  to qualify interest.<br /><strong>2. CRM & Sales Operations</strong><br />Maintain sales/admin system by logging all client interactions.  Clean and organize data to ensure the sales funnel remains accurate and up-to-date.  Track monthly sales and KPIs.<br /><strong>3. Sales Support & Collateral</strong><br />Assist in creating tailored pitch decks, proposals, and quotations using PowerPoint or Canva.  Conduct market research on competitors. Prepare and assist in client meetings.<br /><strong>4. Client Engagement</strong><br />Shadow senior staff during sales calls or product demonstrations to learn closing techniques.  Follow up with inactive leads to re-engage them with new promotions or product updates.  Help manage logistics for sales events, roadshows, or exhibitions.<br /><br />You will work in a dynamic environment under senior leadership.  You will be guided and learn the art of persuasion, develop professional resilience, and build a high-value network of industry leaders. This role will enable you to learn how to solve real-world business problems and understanding the mechanics of sales and revenue generation. </p>",
